@node Requirements
@{b}System requirements@{ub}@{par}
@{par}
@{b}The following is needed :@{ub}@{par}
@{par}
 · AMIGA System with OS 3.0 or above (sorry guys !)@{par}
 · BlueEyes are created for Screens with a 4:3 relation (800*600 for example)@{par}
 · the following librarys are also needed :@{par}
    commodities.library@{par}
    icon.library@{par}
    gadtools.library@{par}
    graphics.library@{par}
    intuition.library@{par}
    utility.library@{par}
    mathieeedoubbas.library@{par}
    mathieeedoubtrans.library@{par}
@{par}
@{par}
@{b}BlueEyes was tested on :@{ub}@{par}
@{par}
 · A3000		OS3.1 10Mb HD Merlin GFX@{par}
 · A4000/40	OS3.0 14Mb HD Retina (Cyber)GFX@{par}
 · A4000/30	OS3.0 18Mb HD Piccolo (Cyber)GFX@{par}
 · A1200		OS3.0  2Mb HD (up to Version 2.2)@{par}
 · DraCo (up to Version 1.2a)@{par}
@{par}
@endnode

@node menu

@{b}The Menu of BlueEyes@{par}
@{par}
Project @{ub}@{par}
@{par}
@{b}save @{ub}@{par}
Saves the X- and Y- position in Tooltypes XPos and YPos.
The Tooltypes XPOS and YPOS must be available !!!@{par}

@{b}about @{ub}@{par}
shows the Copyright Requester@{par}

@{b}quit @{ub}@{par}
removes BlueEyes@{par}

@endnode


@node ToolTypes

@{b}The ToolTypes of BlueEyes@{ub}@{par}
@{par}
BlueEyes has several ToolTypes. If you don`t use it, BlueEyes
use the default-setup.@{par}

@{b}XPos @{ub} (default = 400)@{par}
X-position of the Eyes.@{par}

@{b}YPos @{ub} (default = 1)@{par}
Y-position of the Eyes.@{par}

@{b}SleepTime @{ub}@{par}
Time in 1/10 sec. before BlueEyes go asleep.@{par}

@{b}BlinkTime @{ub} @{par}
Time in 1/10 sec. between the eyelid winks.@{par}

@{b}BackColor @{ub} (default=2)@{par}
The number of the colourregister for the Eyewindow-Background. This is very
useful if you use such tools as Fullbench, or if you want to place BlueEyes
on the WB-Background.@{par}
If you set BackColor to a negativ value, for example -4, then BlueEyes
is using the last 4th color of the Amiga OS-Colorlist.@{par}

@{b}Locked @{ub}@{par}
If this Tooltype used, is it impossible to move the Eyes window.@{par}
It is locked.@{par}

@{b}LowColor@{ub}@{par}
On this Tooltype, BlueEyes is using less of colourregisters. On Screens with less
than 16 colours it is possible that BlueEys looks very ugly. Then you should set
this Tooltype.@{par}

@{b}ToolPri @{ub} (default = 0) AmigaOS function@{par}
The Taskpriority of BlueEyes@{par}

@{b}NoSound @{ub}@{par}
If this Tooltype used, no sound-ID`s are sended to UPD-port (PLAY).@{par}

@{b}Startpri @{ub} (default = 0) AmigaOS function@{par}
Startpriority for BlueEyes. The range is set from -127 (late) to 128 (early).@{par}


The AMIGA Standard ToolTypes for Commodities are not supported !@{par}
@endnode


